Say hello to <b>Dawn</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Dawn has been living in her <a href='/home/?user=momof11'>80913-B Cascade Avenue</a> home ever since May 9th, 2007. She enjoys living in Lakeview and loves everything Millsberry has to offer.<br><br>Being very athletic, Dawn enjoys the wide world of sports. She's quite compassionate, so if you need a sympathetic ear, she'll gladly listen to any problem you might have. Dawn also claims to be modest, and it's no wonder. She's probably had enough practice her modesty with her collection of 12 trophies. <br><br>Dawn enjoys reading, mysteries, and hiking. The hiking comes in handy when she's bouncing back and forth between some of her favorite hangout spots, including the Ice-Rink and the Zoo. Although, we're not sure why Dawn would need to go to the Zoo when she has a wide array of pets ranging from a parrots to iguanas.<br><br>If you are going to pay Dawn a visit, try to bring a couple of other friends with you. You can all practice your technique as team on her very own bobsled. You might want to bring some ice too while you're at it.<br><br>If you happen to bump into Dawn, congratulate her and thank her for being such a great citizen.<br></div>
